State of siege in San Rafael Mine in Guatemala. Photo shared by James
Rodriguez in the MiMundo.org Facebook page

  

> Residents of four towns east of Guatemala's capital woke up to news that
> their communities had been placed under a 30-day state of emergency by the
> administration of President Otto Perez Molina, following anti-mining
> protests that turned violent.

Xeni Jardin reports on the state of siege in the San Rafael Mine for
[BoingBoing](http://boingboing.net/2013/05/02/guatemala-state-of-
emergency.html). Photojournalist James Rodriguez shares photos on his Facebook
page
[MiMundo.org](https://www.facebook.com/pages/MiMundoorg/104827479621741?sk=photos_stream).

